{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I normally teach courses on"},{"time":3000,"text":"how to rebuild states after war."},{"time":7000,"text":"But today I've got a personal story to share with you."},{"time":9000,"text":"This is a picture of my family,"},{"time":12000,"text":"my four siblings -- my mom and I -- taken in 1977."},{"time":16000,"text":"And we're actually Cambodians."},{"time":18000,"text":"And this picture is taken in Vietnam."},{"time":20000,"text":"So how did a Cambodian family end up in Vietnam in 1977?"},{"time":24000,"text":"Well to explain that, I've got a short video clip"},{"time":27000,"text":"to explain the Khmer Rouge regime"},{"time":29000,"text":"during 1975 and 1979."}]},{"cues":[{"time":32000,"text":"Video: April 17th, 1975."},{"time":36000,"text":"The communist Khmer Rouge"},{"time":38000,"text":"enters Phnom Penh to liberate their people"},{"time":41000,"text":"from the encroaching conflict in Vietnam,"},{"time":43000,"text":"and American bombing campaigns."},{"time":47000,"text":"Led by peasant-born Pol Pot,"},{"time":50000,"text":"the Khmer Rouge evacuates people to the countryside"},{"time":54000,"text":"in order to create a rural communist utopia,"},{"time":57000,"text":"much like Mao Tse-tung's Cultural Revolution in China."},{"time":63000,"text":"The Khmer Rouge closes the doors to the outside world."},{"time":67000,"text":"But after four years the grim truth seeps out."},{"time":71000,"text":"In a country of only seven million people,"},{"time":73000,"text":"one and a half million were murdered by their own leaders,"},{"time":77000,"text":"their bodies piled in the mass graves of the killing fields."}]},{"cues":[{"time":81000,"text":"Sophal Ear: So, notwithstanding the 1970s narration,"},{"time":84000,"text":"on April 17th 1975"},{"time":86000,"text":"we lived in Phnom Penh."},{"time":88000,"text":"And my parents were told by the Khmer Rouge"},{"time":91000,"text":"to evacuate the city because of impending American bombing for three days."},{"time":95000,"text":"And here is a picture of the Khmer Rouge."},{"time":97000,"text":"They were young soldiers, typically child soldiers."},{"time":100000,"text":"And this is very normal now, of modern day conflict,"},{"time":103000,"text":"because they're easy to bring into wars."}]},{"cues":[{"time":106000,"text":"The reason that they gave about American bombing wasn't all that far off."},{"time":110000,"text":"I mean, from 1965 to 1973 there were"},{"time":112000,"text":"more munitions that fell on Cambodia"},{"time":116000,"text":"than in all of World War II Japan,"},{"time":118000,"text":"including the two nuclear bombs"},{"time":120000,"text":"of August 1945."},{"time":123000,"text":"The Khmer Rouge didn't believe in money."},{"time":126000,"text":"So the equivalent of the Federal Reserve Bank"},{"time":128000,"text":"in Cambodia was bombed."},{"time":130000,"text":"But not just that, they actually banned money."},{"time":133000,"text":"I think it's the only precedent in which"},{"time":135000,"text":"money has ever been stopped from being used."},{"time":137000,"text":"And we know money is the root of all evil,"},{"time":139000,"text":"but it didn't actually stop evil from happening in Cambodia, in fact."}]},{"cues":[{"time":143000,"text":"My family was moved from Phnom Penh to Pursat province."},{"time":147000,"text":"This is a picture of what Pursat looks like."},{"time":149000,"text":"It's actually a very pretty area of Cambodia,"},{"time":152000,"text":"where rice growing takes place."},{"time":154000,"text":"And in fact they were forced to work the fields."},{"time":156000,"text":"So my father and mother ended up in"},{"time":159000,"text":"a sort of concentration camp, labor camp."}]},{"cues":[{"time":162000,"text":"And it was at that time that my mother got word"},{"time":164000,"text":"from the commune chief"},{"time":167000,"text":"that the Vietnamese were actually asking"},{"time":169000,"text":"for their citizens to go back to Vietnam."},{"time":172000,"text":"And she spoke some Vietnamese,"},{"time":174000,"text":"as a child having grown up with Vietnamese friends."},{"time":177000,"text":"And she decided, despite the advice of her neighbors,"},{"time":181000,"text":"that she would take the chance"},{"time":183000,"text":"and claim to be Vietnamese"},{"time":185000,"text":"so that we could have a chance to survive,"},{"time":187000,"text":"because at this point they're forcing everybody to work."},{"time":189000,"text":"And they're giving about --"},{"time":191000,"text":"in a modern-day, caloric-restriction diet, I guess --"},{"time":194000,"text":"they're giving porridge, with a few grains of rice."}]},{"cues":[{"time":198000,"text":"And at about this time actually"},{"time":200000,"text":"my father got very sick."},{"time":202000,"text":"And he didn't speak Vietnamese."},{"time":204000,"text":"So he died actually, in January 1976."},{"time":207000,"text":"And it made it possible, in fact,"},{"time":210000,"text":"for us to take on this plan."},{"time":212000,"text":"So the Khmer Rouge took us"},{"time":214000,"text":"from a place called Pursat to Kaoh Tiev,"},{"time":216000,"text":"which is across from the border from Vietnam."},{"time":219000,"text":"And there they had a detention camp"},{"time":221000,"text":"where alleged Vietnamese would be tested, language tested."}]},{"cues":[{"time":225000,"text":"And my mother's Vietnamese was so bad"},{"time":228000,"text":"that to make our story more credible,"},{"time":232000,"text":"she'd given all the boys and girls new Vietnamese names."},{"time":235000,"text":"But she'd given the boys girls' names,"},{"time":237000,"text":"and the girls boys' names."},{"time":240000,"text":"And it wasn't until she met a Vietnamese lady"},{"time":242000,"text":"who told her this, and then tutored her for two days intensively,"},{"time":246000,"text":"that she was able to go into her exam"},{"time":249000,"text":"and -- you know, this was a moment of truth."},{"time":252000,"text":"If she fails, we're all headed to the gallows;"},{"time":255000,"text":"if she passes, we can leave to Vietnam."},{"time":257000,"text":"And she actually, of course -- I'm here, she passes."},{"time":261000,"text":"And we end up in Hong Ngu on the Vietnamese side."},{"time":264000,"text":"And then onwards to Chau Doc."},{"time":266000,"text":"And this is a picture of Hong Ngu, Vietnam today."},{"time":268000,"text":"A pretty idyllic place on the Mekong Delta."},{"time":270000,"text":"But for us it meant freedom."},{"time":272000,"text":"And freedom from persecution from the Khmer Rouge."}]},{"cues":[{"time":277000,"text":"Last year, the Khmer Rouge Tribunal,"},{"time":280000,"text":"which the U.N. is helping Cambodia take on,"},{"time":282000,"text":"started, and I decided that as a matter of record"},{"time":284000,"text":"I should file a Civil Complaint"},{"time":287000,"text":"with the Tribunal about my father's passing away."},{"time":290000,"text":"And I got word last month"},{"time":293000,"text":"that the complaint was officially accepted by the Khmer Rouge Tribunal."},{"time":296000,"text":"And it's for me a matter of justice for history, and accountability for the future,"},{"time":301000,"text":"because Cambodia remains a pretty lawless place, at times."}]},{"cues":[{"time":306000,"text":"Five years ago my mother and I went back to Chau Doc."},{"time":310000,"text":"And she was able to return to a place"},{"time":312000,"text":"that for her meant freedom, but also fear,"},{"time":315000,"text":"because we had just come out of Cambodia."},{"time":318000,"text":"I'm happy, actually, today, to present her."},{"time":322000,"text":"She's here today with us in the audience."},{"time":324000,"text":"Thank you mother."}]},{"cues":[{"time":326000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}